<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE; 
</P>
<P>
S. LAKE TAHOE MAYOR SEIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The mayor of South Lake Tahoe, his wife and 16 other people have been arrested 
in connection with a 20-month undercover drug and money-laundering 
investigation, authorities said. Mayor Terry Trupp and his wife, Kim, were 
taken into custody on federal conspiracy and money-laundering charges involving 
alleged efforts to launder about $750,000 to FBI and Internal Revenue Service 
agents, officials said. The Trupps, who are being held without bail in El 
Dorado County Jail, will be arraigned today before a federal magistrate. 
Besides the 18 arrested in the probe, dubbed "Deep Snow," authorities recovered 
about 12 kilograms of cocaine in arrests and seizures, agents said. No drugs 
were seized in the Trupps' arrests, investigators said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
