<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: SOCKERS HAVE GOOD REASON FOR CELEBRATING TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Sockers, who won their seventh indoor soccer championship Saturday night in 
Baltimore, will be treated to a celebration tonight at 6:30 at the San Diego 
Sports Arena. 
</P>
<P>
The players will be brought in by limousine, introduced and presented with 
championship medallions. Speeches will be given by players and Socker Coach Ron 
Newman. 
</P>
<P>
The Sockers defeated the Baltimore Blast, 6-5, in Game 7 to win the Major 
Indoor Soccer League championship. 
</P>
<P>
The San Diego Nomads set a Western Soccer League record by winning their 
seventh consecutive game in a 2-1 victory over the California Kickers. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Paterson, a graduate of Mira Mesa High, scored both goals for the Nomads 
in the second half. It was the second consecutive game in which Coach Derek 
Armstrong switched Paterson from midfield to a forward position after halftime 
and received a two-goal dividend. 
</P>
<P>
Thien Nguyen assisted on one of Paterson's goals and has now contributed an 
assist in six consecutive games, another league record. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Boardman got the other assist. 
</P>
</TEXT>
