</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jet Engine Maker to Double Output: CFM International, a joint venture between 
France's SNECMA and the U.S. giant General Electric Co., announced new orders 
worth $1.5 billion and plans to nearly double its output of jet engines in the 
next three years. Jean Bilien, CFM chairman, reported orders for at least 250 
engines from Beverly Hills-based International Lease Finance Corp., one of 
several aircraft leasing firms that have placed huge orders with Boeing and 
Airbus. The order is for at least 200 CFM-56 and 50 GE CF6-80C2 engines for 
Boeing, Airbus and McDonnell Douglas planes. 
</P>
