<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
India Refuses Trade Talks: India will not negotiate with the U.S. over its 
citation for violating the U.S. Omnibus Trade Act, the Press Trust of India 
reported. Last month, the United States cited India under section 301 of the 
1988 trade act for impeding direct foreign investment and closing the Indian 
insurance market to foreign firms. The law allows the United States to levy 
tariffs of 100% on Indian goods if negotiations fail to remove the barriers 
within 18 months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
