Note: Cost data was calculated by The Times based on terminal size and expense 
information supplied by airport or airline officials. The data can mislead. For 
example, Albuquerque and Los Angeles both doubled the size of an existing 
terminal, so square footage includes old as well as new space. The remodeled 
Los Angeles terminal (Delta Airlines) utilizes more expensive materials, 
including marble and exotic tropical plants, and has more gates. But 
Albuquerque's gates are open to all airlines and serve more daily flights. 
