<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: WESTMINSTER; 
</P>
<P>
PARK TO BE RENAMED IN HONOR OF LATE MAYOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A ceremony to rededicate McFadden Park as Elden F. Gillespie Park, in honor of 
the mayor who died on Feb. 6, 1988, will be held Wednesday at 11 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Gillespie had been a member of the Parks and Recreation Commission for 12 years 
until his appointment to the City Council in 1973. He died at age 71, while 
mayor, after a long bout with cancer. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, a "Pause for the Pledge" program will also be held as part of the 
city's seventh annual Flag Day festivities. 
</P>
<P>
The park is at 9801 McFadden Ave. 
</P>
</TEXT>
