<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: WESTMINSTER; 
</P>
<P>
MAN HIT BY GUNFIRE AT PARTY; SUSPECT HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Saturday evening party turned ugly when one man was shot in the hip and 
another was arrested for attempted murder. 
</P>
<P>
"It was a gathering that went sour," Westminster police Lt. Andrew Hall said. 
</P>
<P>
The evening began quietly enough, Hall said, when victim Pablo Ramirez Diaz, 
32, of Westminster met several friends in a parking lot at 8421 15th St. to 
socialize and watch a portable TV. 
</P>
<P>
But two of the party-goers began to quarrel, Hall said, and one grabbed a 
.45-caliber handgun. 
</P>
<P>
Diaz, who was not involved in the argument, tried to get out of the way but was 
hit in the hip by a single round from the gun. 
</P>
<P>
Diaz was taken by a friend to Humana Hospital-Westminster, where he was 
reported in stable condition Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the man suspected of shooting Diaz fled in his car but was arrested 
later when he returned to the area where the party was held. 
</P>
<P>
"It makes it real easy when they drive back. . . . It wasn't brilliant police 
work," Hall said. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested on suspicion of attempted murder was Eleazar Valle Rangel, 23, of 
Westminster. 
</P>
</TEXT>
