<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
CAL STATE LONG BEACH RANKED NO. 7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach was ranked seventh in the nation in the final Collegiate 
Baseball-ESPN baseball poll of the season, taken after Wichita State captured 
its first national title Saturday with a 5-3 Victory over Texas in the College 
World Series. 
</P>
<P>
Following the Shockers and the Longhorns in the rankings were Florida State, 
Louisiana State, Miami of Florida and Arkansas. Ranked below the 49ers and 
rounding out the top 10 were North Carolina, Texas A&amp;M and Mississippi 
State. The poll is a compilation of votes by 103 coaches, sports writers and 
sports information directors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
